cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper deals with deep neural networks, their compression, and their potential hardware implementation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of ternary connect for neural network compression, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the potential benefits of hardware implementation, which could fall under the category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
